§ Why ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ What is the best estimator for a real-value random variable
    if we consider the squared loss. ⦉
⦉

§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We want to estimate a random variable $x: Ω → 𝗥^n$ from a
    random variable $y: Ω → 𝗥^n$ using an estimator $φ: 𝗥^m →
    𝗥^n$. ⦉
⦉

<statement type='proposition'>
  ‖ The mmse estimator is the conditional mean. ⦉
</statement>
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $x:Ω→𝗥^n$ and $y: Ω → 𝗥^m$. ⦉

  ‖ A ❬minimum mean squared error estimator❭ or ❬MMSE estimator❭
    or ❬least square estimator❭ for $x$ given $y$ is an
    estimator $f: 𝗥^m → 𝗥^n$ which minimizes $𝗘 \norm{f(x) -
    y}^2$. ⦉
⦉

